sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>quay.io/modh<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant AuthProxy as Auth Proxy Sidecar<br/>(oauth-proxy / kube-rbac-proxy)
    participant Workbench as Workbench Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Workbench: Flow 1: User Launches Workbench

    User->>Dashboard: Browse available workbenches<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, OAuth2
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS 1.2+, ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Notebook CR event
    Controller->>Registry: Pull workbench image<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, Registry credentials
    Registry-->>Controller: Container image layers
    Controller->>AuthProxy: Inject auth sidecar<br/>+ create Route/HTTPRoute
    Controller->>Workbench: Start workbench container
    User->>AuthProxy: Access workbench UI<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, OAuth2/RBAC
    AuthProxy->>Workbench: Forward authenticated request<br/>HTTP/8888 (internal)
    Workbench-->>AuthProxy: JupyterLab/code-server/RStudio UI
    AuthProxy-->>User: Rendered UI response

    Note over User,Workbench: Flow 2: RStudio BuildConfig Build (On-Cluster)

    participant BuildCtrl as OpenShift Build Controller
    participant GitHub as GitHub Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RHEL as registry.access.redhat.com<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    BuildCtrl->>GitHub: Fetch Dockerfile + context<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, Public
    GitHub-->>BuildCtrl: Source code
    BuildCtrl->>RHEL: Pull base image<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, Pull secret
    RHEL-->>BuildCtrl: UBI9 base image
    BuildCtrl->>K8sAPI: Push to ImageStream<br/>Internal

    Note over User,Workbench: Flow 3: Elyra Pipeline Execution

    participant DSP as Data Science Pipelines API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Runtime as Runtime Pod<br/>(runtime image)
    participant S3 as S3 / Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Workbench->>DSP: Submit pipeline<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, Bearer Token
    DSP->>Registry: Pull runtime image<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, Registry credentials
    Registry-->>DSP: Runtime image
    DSP->>Runtime: Execute pipeline node
    Runtime->>S3: Read/write data artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, AWS credentials
    S3-->>Runtime: Data artifacts
    Runtime-->>DSP: Pipeline node result
